# Exclude build outputs from the docker build context.
#
# Without this, `COPY BusTerminal.Api/ BusTerminal.Api/` in the Dockerfile
# would pull in any host-side `bin/` and `obj/` directories produced by local
# `dotnet build` / `dotnet test` and overlay them on top of the freshly
# restored container-side `obj/`. The mismatch surfaces at publish time as
# `NETSDK1064: Package <name>, version <v> was not found. It might have been
# deleted since NuGet restore.` (the package IS restored — the host's stale
# `obj/project.assets.json` points at a different package graph than the
# container's). CI never tripped this because runners start from a clean
# checkout, but it breaks local `docker build` for any contributor with prior
# `dotnet` activity in this tree.

**/bin/
**/obj/
**/*.user
**/.vs/
**/TestResults/

# Exclude things that have nothing to do with the runtime image.
**/*.md
**/.dockerignore
**/.gitignore
**/.editorconfig
